725636f-a.text: 74th Street, north from and across 34th Avenue, showing the thoroughfares and new apartment houses being constructed on former farmland along the west side of the old Trains Meadow Road. October 21, 1936. P. L. Sperr.

725637f-a.text: 76th Street, east side, between 35th and 34th Avenues, showing an old cottage, which was either the J. Johnson or Bartley property in 1873. It was then on Trains Meadow Road, now no longer in existence. October 21, 1936. P. L. Sperr.
